                                                                           FileWriter

    Constructors
       FileWriter fw = new FileWriter("Cool.txt"); This method is for overriding the concept
       FileWriter fw = new FileWriter("Cool.txt",true);  This method is for appending the content
       FileWriter fw = new FileWriter(f,true);
       FileWriter fw = new FileWriter(f);  :-where f is the file reference point to the file object

    METHODS IN FileWriter.

       write(int ch);  to write one character into the file
       write(char [] ch) ; to write an array of characters
       write(String name) : to write String to the file
       fw.flush();  // to give the guarantee that total data including last character will be written to the file.
       fw.close();  // to close the writer
